You may be right. But that's what the documentation says to do.  The example in the manual, at
http://doc.rust-lang.org/regex/regex/index.html
reads

``` #![feature(plugin)]
#[plugin] #[no_link]
extern crate regex_macros;
extern crate regex;

fn main() {
    let re = regex!(r"^\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2}$");
    assert_eq!(re.is_match("2014-01-01"), true);
}
```

"regex_macros" is a crate within the "regex" crate. There's a .toml file under another .toml file. That's probably confusing something in the build/link system.
